==English==
===Etymology===
from [[candle]] + [[-mas]], following the tradition that the candles to be used in church during the following year are [[bless]]ed on this day
===Pronunciation===
(IPA) US: /ˈkændəlməs/
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Candlemas'''
# The [[festival]] in the [[Christian]] year that [[commemorate]]s the [[purification]] of the [[Virgin Mary]] and the [[presentation]] of the [[infant]] [[Jesus]] in the [[Temple]] 
#: February 2nd in the western [[Christian]] church and February 15th in the [[Orthodox]] church.
# A [[quarter day]] in [[Scotland]].

